{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RQxoDgBJV6Z6YQQGGfUb8r","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→@use \"palette\" as *;\n     2→@use \"glass\" as *;\n     3→\n     4→// Islands — ChamferedBar handles glass background via Cairo\n     5→// CSS provides only min-height and padding for pointed tips\n     6→.island-left {\n     7→  min-height: 26px;\n     8→  padding-right: 16px; // keep children clear of the pointed right tip\n     9→}\n    10→\n    11→.island-center {\n    12→  min-height: 26px;\n    13→}\n    14→\n    15→.island-right {\n    16→  min-height: 26px;\n    17→  padding-left: 16px; // keep children clear of the pointed left tip\n    18→}\n    19→\n    20→.tiled-bar {\n    21→  min-height: 26px;\n    22→}\n    23→\n    24→.segment {\n    25→  padding: 0px 8px;\n    26→  min-height: 26px;\n    27→  color: $text-primary;\n    28→}\n    29→\n    30→// System tray: hide menubutton dropdown arrows\n    31→.segment-tray menubutton {\n    32→  background: transparent;\n    33→  border: none;\n    34→  padding: 0px 2px;\n    35→  min-width: 0px;\n    36→}\n    37→\n    38→.segment-tray menubutton > box > image:last-child {\n    39→  min-width: 0px;\n    40→  min-height: 0px;\n    41→}\n    42→\n    43→// Service status icons (Gio.FileIcon doesn't respect CSS color,\n    44→// so we use opacity for health indication instead)\n    45→.svc-icon {\n    46→  opacity: 1.0;\n    47→  transition: opacity 300ms ease;\n    48→}\n    49→\n    50→.svc-error {\n    51→  opacity: 0.35;\n    52→}\n    53→\n    54→// System tray collapse/expand toggle\n    55→.tray-toggle {\n    56→  background: transparent;\n    57→  border: none;\n    58→  color: $text-primary;\n    59→  font-size: 14px;\n    60→  padding: 0px 2px;\n    61→  min-width: 0px;\n    62→  min-height: 0px;\n    63→\n    64→  &:hover {\n    65→    color: $text-secondary;\n    66→  }\n    67→}\n    68→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lcwbe1yp9R1GGktAn9xgGR","session_id":"87de7f8a-1210-4ae0-aa43-0a98da4aea22","uuid":"080bea01-2521-4a5f-8e9c-55f659a4870e","timestamp":"2026-03-17T11:24:55.344Z"}
