{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lcwbe1yp9R1GGktAn9xgGR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report: AGS Notification Center\n\n### 1. FULL DIRECTORY LISTING\n\n```\n/home/kiriketsuki/dots/chrysaki-ralph-ags-notification-center-T10/ags/.config/ags/\n├── app.ts                                    (Main entry point)\n├── env.d.ts                                  (TypeScript declarations)\n├── style.scss                                (Master stylesheet)\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── package.json\n├── .gitignore\n├── icons/\n│   └── hicolor/scalable/status/\n│       ├── gitnexus-symbolic.svg\n│       ├── ollama-symbolic.svg\n│       ├── openviking-symbolic.svg\n│       └── syncthing-symbolic.svg\n├── lib/                                      (Utility libraries)\n│   ├── wave-state.ts\n│   ├── border-wave-state.ts\n│   ├── cairo-hex.ts\n│   ├── cairo-island.ts\n│   ├── cairo-triangles.ts\n│   ├── cairo-separator.ts\n│   └── tiling.ts\n├── styles/                                   (SCSS partials)\n│   ├── _palette.scss\n│   ├── _glass.scss\n│   ├── _bar.scss\n│   ├── _workspaces.scss\n│   ├── _clock.scss\n│   ├── _battery.scss\n│   ├── _active-window.scss\n│   ├── _notifications.scss\n│   ├── _powermenu.scss\n│   ├── _pulseaudio.scss\n│   ├── _services.scss\n│   ├── _utility-buttons.scss\n│   └── _should-have.scss\n└── widgets/                                  (React/TSX components)\n    ├── BarLeft.tsx\n    ├── BarCenter.tsx\n    ├── BarRight.tsx\n    ├── NotificationCenter.tsx\n    ├── NotificationToggle.tsx\n    ├── ActiveWindow.tsx\n    ├── Battery.tsx\n    ├── Clock.tsx\n    ├── MediaPlayer.tsx\n    ├── Network.tsx\n    ├── PulseAudio.tsx\n    ├── PowerMenu.tsx\n    ├── ServiceStatus.tsx\n    ├── SystemTray.tsx\n    ├── ThemeButton.tsx\n    ├── WallpaperButton.tsx\n    ├── TiledSegment.tsx\n    └── ChamferedIsland.tsx\n```\n\n**STATUS**: NotificationToast.tsx is referenced in app.ts (line 8) but does not exist yet — needs to be created.\n\n---\n\n### 2. FULL CONTENT: app.ts\n\n```typescript\nimport app from \"ags/gtk4/app\"\nimport style from \"./style.scss\"\nimport { BarLeft } from \"./widgets/BarLeft\"\nimport { BarCenter } from \"./widgets/BarCenter\"\nimport { BarRight } from \"./widgets/BarRight\"\nimport { ServicePanel } from \"./widgets/ServiceStatus\"\nimport { NotificationCenter } from \"./widgets/NotificationCenter\"\nimport { NotificationToast } from \"./widgets/NotificationToast\"\n\napp.start({\n  instanceName: \"chrysaki-bar\",\n  css: style,\n  main() {\n    app.get_monitors().map((monitor) => {\n      BarLeft(monitor)\n      BarCenter(monitor)\n      BarRight(monitor)\n    })\n    // Single-instance panels (not per-monitor)\n    ServicePanel()\n    NotificationCenter()\n    NotificationToast()\n  },\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. FULL CONTENT: NotificationCenter.tsx\n\n```typescript\nimport app from \"ags/gtk4/app\"\nimport { createBinding } from \"ags\"\nimport { Astal } from \"ags/gtk4\"\nimport AstalNotifd from \"gi://AstalNotifd\"\n\nconst PANEL_NAME = \"chrysaki-notification-center\"\n\nexport const notifd = AstalNotifd.get_default()!\n\n// --- Unread count (module-level state, no GObject needed) ---\n\nlet _unreadCount = 0\nconst _unreadListeners: Array<() => void> = []\n\nfunction _setUnreadCount(n: number): void {\n  _unreadCount = Math.max(0, n)\n  _unreadListeners.forEach((cb) => cb())\n}\n\nexport function getUnreadCount(): number {\n  return _unreadCount\n}\n\nexport function onUnreadChange(cb: () => void): void {\n  _unreadListeners.push(cb)\n}\n\nnotifd.connect(\"notified\", () => {\n  _setUnreadCount(_unreadCount + 1)\n})\n\n// --- Panel toggle ---\n\nexport function toggleNotificationCenter(): void {\n  const panel = app.get_window(PANEL_NAME)\n  if (panel) {\n    if (!panel.visible) {\n      _setUnreadCount(0)\n    }\n    panel.visible = !panel.visible\n  }\n}\n\n// --- Notification list helpers ---\n\n// Sanitize a freedesktop.org HTML notification body to safe Pango markup.\n// The spec allows a small HTML subset (<b>, <i>, <u>, <a>, <img>, <br>).\n// Pango supports <b>, <i>, <u>, <s>, <tt>, <span>, <sub>, <sup>, <big>, <small>.\n// Returns the processed string and whether Pango markup mode should be enabled.\nfunction sanitizeBodyMarkup(body: string): { markup: string; hasMarkup: boolean } {\n  if (!/<[a-zA-Z]/.test(body)) {\n    return { markup: body, hasMarkup: false }\n  }\n  const PANGO_SAFE = new Set([\n    \"b\",\n    \"i\",\n    \"u\",\n    \"s\",\n    \"tt\",\n    \"span\",\n    \"sub\",\n    \"sup\",\n    \"big\",\n    \"small\",\n  ])\n  const markup = body\n    // <br> and <br/> → newline\n    .replace(/<br\\s*\\/?>/gi, \"\\n\")\n    // Strip <img> entirely (no visual equivalent in Pango)\n    .replace(/<img\\b[^>]*>/gi, \"\")\n    // Strip <a> open/close tags — keep link text, Pango has no href rendering\n    .replace(/<a\\b[^>]*>/gi, \"\")\n    .replace(/<\\/a>/gi, \"\")\n    // Pass Pango-safe tags through; strip everything else\n    .replace(\n      /<\\/?\\s*([a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*)(\\s[^>]*)?\\s*>/g,\n      (match, tag: string) => (PANGO_SAFE.has(tag.toLowerCase()) ? match : \"\"),\n    )\n  return { markup, hasMarkup: true }\n}\n\nfunction BodyLabel({ body }: { body: string }) {\n  const { markup, hasMarkup } = sanitizeBodyMarkup(body)\n  return (\n    <label\n      class=\"notif-row-body\"\n      label={markup}\n      useMarkup={hasMarkup}\n      halign={1}\n      xalign={0}\n      wrap\n      ellipsize={3}\n    />\n  )\n}\n\nfunction formatTimestamp(unixTime: number): string {\n  const nowSec = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000)\n  const diff = nowSec - unixTime\n  if (diff < 60) return \"just now\"\n  if (diff < 3600) return `${Math.floor(diff / 60)}m ago`\n  if (diff < 86400) return `${Math.floor(diff / 3600)}h ago`\n  return `${Math.floor(diff / 86400)}d ago`\n}\n\nfunction NotificationRow(n: AstalNotifd.Notification) {\n  const isCritical = n.urgency === AstalNotifd.Urgency.CRITICAL\n  return (\n    <box\n      class={`notif-row${isCritical ? \" notif-row-critical\" : \"\"}`}\n      orientation={1}\n      spacing={2}\n    >\n      <box class=\"notif-row-header\" spacing={6}>\n        <label\n          class=\"notif-row-app\"\n          label={n.appName || \"App\"}\n          halign={1}\n          hexpand\n        />\n        <label\n          class=\"notif-row-time\"\n          label={formatTimestamp(n.time)}\n          halign={2}\n        />\n        <button\n          class=\"notif-dismiss-btn\"\n          label=\"󰅖\"\n          onClicked={() => n.dismiss()}\n        />\n      </box>\n      <label\n        class=\"notif-row-summary\"\n        label={n.summary || \"\"}\n        halign={1}\n        xalign={0}\n        wrap\n      />\n      {n.body && <BodyLabel body={n.body} />}\n      {n.actions.length > 0 && (\n        <box class=\"notif-actions\" spacing={4}>\n          {n.actions.map((action) => (\n            <button\n              class=\"notif-action-btn\"\n              label={action.label}\n              hexpand\n              onClicked={() => n.invokeAction(action.id)}\n            />\n          ))}\n        </box>\n      )}\n    </box>\n  )\n}\n\n// --- Clear-all button ---\n\nfunction ClearAllButton() {\n  const notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\n  return (\n    <button\n      class=\"notif-clear-all-btn\"\n      label=\"󰆴  Clear all\"\n      visible={notifications.as((list) => list.length > 0)}\n      onClicked={() => {\n        const list = [...notifd.notifications]\n        list.forEach((n) => n.dismiss())\n        _setUnreadCount(0)\n      }}\n    />\n  )\n}\n\n// --- DND toggle (header button) ---\n\nfunction DndToggle() {\n  const dnd = createBinding(notifd, \"dontDisturb\")\n  return (\n    <button\n      class={dnd.as((on) => `notif-dnd-btn${on ? \" notif-dnd-active\" : \"\"}`)}\n      label={dnd.as((on) => (on ? \"󰂛\" : \"󰂚\"))}\n      tooltipText={dnd.as((on) =>\n        on ? \"DND on — click to disable\" : \"DND off — click to enable\",\n      )}\n      onClicked={() => {\n        notifd.dontDisturb = !notifd.dontDisturb\n      }}\n    />\n  )\n}\n\n// --- Panel window ---\n\nexport function NotificationCenter() {\n  const { TOP, RIGHT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n  const notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\n\n  return (\n    <window\n      name={PANEL_NAME}\n      namespace={PANEL_NAME}\n      visible={false}\n      anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n      marginTop={48}\n      marginRight={8}\n      application={app}\n    >\n      <box class=\"notif-panel\" orientation={1} spacing={0}>\n        <box class=\"notif-panel-header\" spacing={4}>\n          <label\n            class=\"notif-panel-title\"\n            label=\"󰂚  Notifications\"\n            halign={1}\n            hexpand\n          />\n          <ClearAllButton />\n          <DndToggle />\n        </box>\n        <box class=\"notif-panel-list\" orientation={1} spacing={4}>\n          {notifications.as((list) =>\n            list.length === 0\n              ? [\n                  <label\n                    class=\"notif-empty\"\n                    label=\"No notifications\"\n                    halign={3}\n                    valign={3}\n                  />,\n                ]\n              : [...list].reverse().map((n) => NotificationRow(n)),\n          )}\n        </box>\n      </box>\n    </window>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. FULL CONTENT: NotificationToggle.tsx\n\n```typescript\nimport { getUnreadCount, onUnreadChange, toggleNotificationCenter } from \"./NotificationCenter\"\n\nexport function NotificationToggle() {\n  return (\n    <box class=\"notif-toggle-wrap\" valign={3}>\n      <button\n        class=\"utility-button\"\n        label=\"󰂚\"\n        onClicked={() => toggleNotificationCenter()}\n        tooltipText=\"Toggle notifications\"\n      />\n      <label\n        class=\"notif-badge\"\n        visible={false}\n        label=\"\"\n        valign={1}\n        $={(self: any) => {\n          function update() {\n            const count = getUnreadCount()\n            if (count > 0) {\n              self.label = count > 9 ? \"9+\" : String(count)\n              self.visible = true\n            } else {\n              self.label = \"\"\n              self.visible = false\n            }\n          }\n          onUnreadChange(update)\n        }}\n      />\n    </box>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. FULL CONTENT: _notifications.scss\n\n```scss\n@use \"palette\" as *;\n\n// ============================================================\n// Bar toggle button\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-toggle-wrap {\n  position: relative;\n}\n\n// Flat-top hexagon badge (Chrysaki status indicator shape)\n.notif-badge {\n  clip-path: polygon(25% 0%, 75% 0%, 100% 50%, 75% 100%, 25% 100%, 0% 50%);\n  background: $error;\n  color: $text-primary;\n  font-size: 9px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n  min-width: 16px;\n  min-height: 16px;\n  padding: 0px 2px;\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Panel window (glassmorphism — compositor blur provides depth)\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-panel {\n  background-color: rgba(15, 17, 23, 0.15);\n  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);\n  box-shadow: 0 8px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);\n  padding: 10px;\n  min-width: 320px;\n  max-width: 400px;\n}\n\n// --- Panel header ---\n\n.notif-panel-header {\n  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);\n  padding-bottom: 6px;\n  margin-bottom: 4px;\n}\n\n.notif-panel-title {\n  color: $text-primary;\n  font-size: 15px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n  padding: 4px 0px;\n}\n\n.notif-clear-all-btn {\n  background: transparent;\n  border: none;\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 11px;\n  padding: 2px 6px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    color: $error;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-dnd-btn {\n  background: transparent;\n  border: none;\n  color: $text-secondary;\n  font-size: 16px;\n  padding: 2px 4px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    color: $text-primary;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-dnd-active {\n  color: $blonde-light;\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Panel notification list\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-panel-list {\n  padding: 4px 0px;\n}\n\n.notif-empty {\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  padding: 16px 0px;\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Notification row (chamfered Chrysaki container)\n// clip-path produces the 8px chamfer; borders are omitted as\n// clip-path clips them off — use background tint instead.\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-row {\n  clip-path: polygon(\n    8px 0%,\n    calc(100% - 8px) 0%,\n    100% 8px,\n    100% calc(100% - 8px),\n    calc(100% - 8px) 100%,\n    8px 100%,\n    0% calc(100% - 8px),\n    0% 8px\n  );\n  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);\n  padding: 8px 12px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);\n  }\n}\n\n// Urgency modifier: critical notifications get Error red tint\n.notif-row-critical {\n  background: rgba(140, 47, 57, 0.15);\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(140, 47, 57, 0.25);\n  }\n\n  .notif-row-app {\n    color: $blonde-light;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-row-header {\n  margin-bottom: 2px;\n}\n\n.notif-row-app {\n  color: $teal-light;\n  font-size: 11px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n.notif-row-time {\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 10px;\n}\n\n.notif-dismiss-btn {\n  background: transparent;\n  border: none;\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  padding: 0px 2px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    color: $error;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-row-summary {\n  color: $text-primary;\n  font-size: 13px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n.notif-row-body {\n  color: $text-secondary;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  margin-top: 2px;\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Notification action buttons\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-actions {\n  margin-top: 6px;\n  padding-top: 4px;\n  border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);\n}\n\n.notif-action-btn {\n  background: rgba(26, 138, 106, 0.15);\n  border: 1px solid rgba(26, 138, 106, 0.3);\n  color: $emerald-light;\n  font-size: 11px;\n  padding: 3px 8px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(26, 138, 106, 0.3);\n    border-color: $emerald-light;\n    color: $text-primary;\n  }\n\n  &:active {\n    background: rgba(26, 138, 106, 0.45);\n  }\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Toast popup window (layer-shell, TOP | RIGHT anchor)\n// High alpha background: toasts float without compositor blur.\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-toast-list {\n  padding: 0px;\n}\n\n// Chamfered toast card — matches .notif-row shape at larger scale\n.notif-toast {\n  clip-path: polygon(\n    8px 0%,\n    calc(100% - 8px) 0%,\n    100% 8px,\n    100% calc(100% - 8px),\n    calc(100% - 8px) 100%,\n    8px 100%,\n    0% calc(100% - 8px),\n    0% 8px\n  );\n  background: rgba(28, 31, 43, 0.92); // $surface at high alpha\n  padding: 10px 14px;\n  min-width: 300px;\n  max-width: 380px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(37, 40, 54, 0.95); // $raised at high alpha\n  }\n}\n\n// Urgency modifier: critical toasts get Error red background\n.notif-toast-critical {\n  background: rgba(140, 47, 57, 0.88);\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(181, 63, 74, 0.92);\n  }\n\n  .notif-toast-app {\n    color: $blonde-light;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-toast-header {\n  margin-bottom: 3px;\n}\n\n.notif-toast-app {\n  color: $emerald-light;\n  font-size: 11px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n.notif-toast-close {\n  background: transparent;\n  border: none;\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  padding: 0px 2px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    color: $error;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-toast-summary {\n  color: $text-primary;\n  font-size: 13px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n.notif-toast-body {\n  color: $text-secondary;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  margin-top: 2px;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. TOAST-RELATED FILES\n\nNo existing `Toast` or `Toast`-related files exist. The toast styles are defined in `_notifications.scss` (lines 202–280), but the TypeScript component `NotificationToast.tsx` has not yet been created.\n\n---\n\n### 7. FULL CONTENT: style.scss\n\n```scss\n@use \"styles/palette\" as *;\n@use \"styles/glass\" as *;\n@use \"styles/bar\";\n@use \"styles/workspaces\";\n@use \"styles/clock\";\n@use \"styles/battery\";\n@use \"styles/powermenu\";\n@use \"styles/should-have\";\n@use \"styles/active-window\";\n@use \"styles/pulseaudio\";\n@use \"styles/utility-buttons\";\n@use \"styles/services\";\n@use \"styles/notifications\";\n\n* {\n  font-family: \"Space Grotesk\", \"IosevkaTermSlab Nerd Font\", monospace;\n  font-size: 13px;\n}\n\nwindow {\n  background: transparent;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. EXAMPLE WINDOW COMPONENTS\n\n#### ServicePanel (ServiceStatus.tsx, lines 164–184)\nA modal panel with TOP | RIGHT anchor showing service health indicators:\n```typescript\nexport function ServicePanel() {\n  const { TOP, RIGHT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n\n  return (\n    <window\n      name={PANEL_NAME}\n      namespace={PANEL_NAME}\n      visible={false}\n      anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n      marginTop={48}\n      marginRight={8}\n      application={app}\n    >\n      <box class=\"svc-panel\" orientation={1} spacing={4}>\n        <label class=\"svc-panel-title\" label={\"\\u{F0614}  Services\"} halign={1} />\n        {SERVICES.map((svc) => ServiceRow(svc))}\n      </box>\n    </window>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n#### NotificationCenter (NotificationCenter.tsx, lines 194–237)\nAnother modal panel at TOP | RIGHT:\n```typescript\nexport function NotificationCenter() {\n  const { TOP, RIGHT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n  const notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\n\n  return (\n    <window\n      name={PANEL_NAME}\n      namespace={PANEL_NAME}\n      visible={false}\n      anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n      marginTop={48}\n      marginRight={8}\n      application={app}\n    >\n      <box class=\"notif-panel\" orientation={1} spacing={0}>\n        {/* panel content */}\n      </box>\n    </window>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n#### BarLeft (per-monitor persistent bar)\nPer-monitor bars are created per the `app.get_monitors()` loop in `app.ts`:\n```typescript\nexport function BarLeft(gdkmonitor: Gdk.Monitor) {\n  const { TOP, LEFT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n\n  return (\n    <window\n      visible\n      name=\"chrysaki-bar-left\"\n      namespace=\"chrysaki-bar-left\"\n      gdkmonitor={gdkmonitor}\n      anchor={TOP | LEFT}\n      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n      marginTop={0}\n      marginLeft={8}\n      application={app}\n    >\n      {/* bar content */}\n    </window>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n**Key pattern**: Persistent bars (like BarLeft, BarRight, BarCenter) are visible by default and per-monitor. Modal panels (like NotificationCenter, ServicePanel) are initially hidden and toggled by button clicks.\n\n---\n\n### 9. ASTAL/NOTIFD API USAGE PATTERNS\n\n#### Import Pattern\n```typescript\nimport AstalNotifd from \"gi://AstalNotifd\"\nconst notifd = AstalNotifd.get_default()!\n```\n\n#### Other Astal Services (examples from codebase)\n```typescript\n// Network\nimport AstalNetwork from \"gi://AstalNetwork\"\nconst network = AstalNetwork.get_default()!\n\n// Media (MPRIS)\nimport AstalMpris from \"gi://AstalMpris\"\nconst mpris = AstalMpris.get_default()!\n```\n\n#### createBinding Pattern (Reactive Property Binding)\n```typescript\nimport { createBinding, createComputed } from \"ags\"\n\n// Bind to a GObject property\nconst notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\nconst dnd = createBinding(notifd, \"dontDisturb\")\n\n// Use in JSX via .as() to transform the binding\nvisible={notifications.as((list) => list.length > 0)}\nlabel={dnd.as((on) => (on ? \"󰂛\" : \"󰂚\"))}\n```\n\n#### Signal Connection Pattern\n```typescript\nnotifd.connect(\"notified\", () => {\n  _setUnreadCount(_unreadCount + 1)\n})\n```\n\n#### Accessing Notification Properties\n```typescript\nfunction NotificationRow(n: AstalNotifd.Notification) {\n  const isCritical = n.urgency === AstalNotifd.Urgency.CRITICAL\n  return (\n    <box>\n      <label label={n.appName || \"App\"} />\n      <label label={n.summary || \"\"} />\n      {n.body && <BodyLabel body={n.body} />}\n      {n.actions.length > 0 && (\n        <box class=\"notif-actions\">\n          {n.actions.map((action) => (\n            <button\n              label={action.label}\n              onClicked={() => n.invokeAction(action.id)}\n            />\n          ))}\n        </box>\n      )}\n      <button onClicked={() => n.dismiss()} />\n    </box>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n#### Window Anchors & Properties\n```typescript\nimport { Astal } from \"ags/gtk4\"\n\nconst { TOP, RIGHT, LEFT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n\n<window\n  name=\"panel-name\"\n  namespace=\"panel-name\"\n  visible={false}\n  anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n  exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n  marginTop={48}\n  marginRight={8}\n  application={app}\n>\n  {/* content */}\n</window>\n```\n\n#### createPoll Pattern (Polling/Time-based Updates)\n```typescript\nimport { createPoll } from \"ags/time\"\n\nconst time = createPoll(\"00:00\", 1000, () => {\n  return `󰥔  ${GLib.DateTime.new_now_local()!.format(\"%H:%M\")!}`\n})\n\n<label label={time} />\n```\n\n#### createComputed Pattern (Derived State)\n```typescript\nimport { createComputed } from \"ags\"\n\nconst isOk = createComputed(() => status().trim() === \"ok\")\nconst statusClass = createComputed(() =>\n  isOk() ? \"svc-panel-healthy\" : \"svc-panel-unhealthy\"\n)\n\n<image class={statusClass} />\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Key Takeaways for Toast Implementation:**\n\n1. **NotificationToast.tsx** must be created in `/home/kiriketsuki/dots/chrysaki-ralph-ags-notification-center-T10/ags/.config/ags/widgets/`\n\n2. **API Access**: Use `notifd` (already exported from `NotificationCenter.tsx`) to listen for notifications and iterate over `notifd.notifications`.\n\n3. **Window Properties**: Toast should use `TOP | RIGHT` anchor with `exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}` to float above other windows without reserving space. Higher `marginTop` than the panel (48px) to avoid collision.\n\n4. **Styling**: CSS classes `.notif-toast`, `.notif-toast-critical`, `.notif-toast-app`, `.notif-toast-summary`, `.notif-toast-body`, `.notif-toast-close` are already defined in `_notifications.scss` (lines 207–279). Use chamfered clip-path matching the panel rows.\n\n5. **Reactive Patterns**: Use `createBinding()` for property reactions, `createComputed()` for derived state, `createPoll()` for time-based updates, and direct signal connections (`notifd.connect()`) for event handling.\n\n6. **Color Palette**: Access via `$palette` SCSS variables. Emerald-light for accents, error for critical urgency, text-primary/secondary for content."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a05e1f4303b0d516d (use SendMessage with to: 'a05e1f4303b0d516d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 101900\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 131025</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87de7f8a-1210-4ae0-aa43-0a98da4aea22","uuid":"905a7e82-83a8-44c6-8c45-1b705e5bdc14","timestamp":"2026-03-17T11:25:53.426Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /home/kiriketsuki/dots/chrysaki-ralph-ags-notification-center-T10/ags/.config/ags/ and return:\n\n1. Full directory listing (all files)\n2. Full content of: app.ts, NotificationCenter.tsx, NotificationToggle.tsx, _notifications.scss\n3. Full content of any existing toast-related files (search for \"Toast\" in filenames)\n4. Full content of style.scss\n5. Examples of existing window components (e.g., ServicePanel.tsx, any panel that uses layer-shell)\n6. The Astal/notifd API usage pattern — check how AstalNotifd is imported and used across existing files\n\nBe thorough — return full file contents, not summaries.","agentId":"a05e1f4303b0d516d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report: AGS Notification Center\n\n### 1. FULL DIRECTORY LISTING\n\n```\n/home/kiriketsuki/dots/chrysaki-ralph-ags-notification-center-T10/ags/.config/ags/\n├── app.ts                                    (Main entry point)\n├── env.d.ts                                  (TypeScript declarations)\n├── style.scss                                (Master stylesheet)\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── package.json\n├── .gitignore\n├── icons/\n│   └── hicolor/scalable/status/\n│       ├── gitnexus-symbolic.svg\n│       ├── ollama-symbolic.svg\n│       ├── openviking-symbolic.svg\n│       └── syncthing-symbolic.svg\n├── lib/                                      (Utility libraries)\n│   ├── wave-state.ts\n│   ├── border-wave-state.ts\n│   ├── cairo-hex.ts\n│   ├── cairo-island.ts\n│   ├── cairo-triangles.ts\n│   ├── cairo-separator.ts\n│   └── tiling.ts\n├── styles/                                   (SCSS partials)\n│   ├── _palette.scss\n│   ├── _glass.scss\n│   ├── _bar.scss\n│   ├── _workspaces.scss\n│   ├── _clock.scss\n│   ├── _battery.scss\n│   ├── _active-window.scss\n│   ├── _notifications.scss\n│   ├── _powermenu.scss\n│   ├── _pulseaudio.scss\n│   ├── _services.scss\n│   ├── _utility-buttons.scss\n│   └── _should-have.scss\n└── widgets/                                  (React/TSX components)\n    ├── BarLeft.tsx\n    ├── BarCenter.tsx\n    ├── BarRight.tsx\n    ├── NotificationCenter.tsx\n    ├── NotificationToggle.tsx\n    ├── ActiveWindow.tsx\n    ├── Battery.tsx\n    ├── Clock.tsx\n    ├── MediaPlayer.tsx\n    ├── Network.tsx\n    ├── PulseAudio.tsx\n    ├── PowerMenu.tsx\n    ├── ServiceStatus.tsx\n    ├── SystemTray.tsx\n    ├── ThemeButton.tsx\n    ├── WallpaperButton.tsx\n    ├── TiledSegment.tsx\n    └── ChamferedIsland.tsx\n```\n\n**STATUS**: NotificationToast.tsx is referenced in app.ts (line 8) but does not exist yet — needs to be created.\n\n---\n\n### 2. FULL CONTENT: app.ts\n\n```typescript\nimport app from \"ags/gtk4/app\"\nimport style from \"./style.scss\"\nimport { BarLeft } from \"./widgets/BarLeft\"\nimport { BarCenter } from \"./widgets/BarCenter\"\nimport { BarRight } from \"./widgets/BarRight\"\nimport { ServicePanel } from \"./widgets/ServiceStatus\"\nimport { NotificationCenter } from \"./widgets/NotificationCenter\"\nimport { NotificationToast } from \"./widgets/NotificationToast\"\n\napp.start({\n  instanceName: \"chrysaki-bar\",\n  css: style,\n  main() {\n    app.get_monitors().map((monitor) => {\n      BarLeft(monitor)\n      BarCenter(monitor)\n      BarRight(monitor)\n    })\n    // Single-instance panels (not per-monitor)\n    ServicePanel()\n    NotificationCenter()\n    NotificationToast()\n  },\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. FULL CONTENT: NotificationCenter.tsx\n\n```typescript\nimport app from \"ags/gtk4/app\"\nimport { createBinding } from \"ags\"\nimport { Astal } from \"ags/gtk4\"\nimport AstalNotifd from \"gi://AstalNotifd\"\n\nconst PANEL_NAME = \"chrysaki-notification-center\"\n\nexport const notifd = AstalNotifd.get_default()!\n\n// --- Unread count (module-level state, no GObject needed) ---\n\nlet _unreadCount = 0\nconst _unreadListeners: Array<() => void> = []\n\nfunction _setUnreadCount(n: number): void {\n  _unreadCount = Math.max(0, n)\n  _unreadListeners.forEach((cb) => cb())\n}\n\nexport function getUnreadCount(): number {\n  return _unreadCount\n}\n\nexport function onUnreadChange(cb: () => void): void {\n  _unreadListeners.push(cb)\n}\n\nnotifd.connect(\"notified\", () => {\n  _setUnreadCount(_unreadCount + 1)\n})\n\n// --- Panel toggle ---\n\nexport function toggleNotificationCenter(): void {\n  const panel = app.get_window(PANEL_NAME)\n  if (panel) {\n    if (!panel.visible) {\n      _setUnreadCount(0)\n    }\n    panel.visible = !panel.visible\n  }\n}\n\n// --- Notification list helpers ---\n\n// Sanitize a freedesktop.org HTML notification body to safe Pango markup.\n// The spec allows a small HTML subset (<b>, <i>, <u>, <a>, <img>, <br>).\n// Pango supports <b>, <i>, <u>, <s>, <tt>, <span>, <sub>, <sup>, <big>, <small>.\n// Returns the processed string and whether Pango markup mode should be enabled.\nfunction sanitizeBodyMarkup(body: string): { markup: string; hasMarkup: boolean } {\n  if (!/<[a-zA-Z]/.test(body)) {\n    return { markup: body, hasMarkup: false }\n  }\n  const PANGO_SAFE = new Set([\n    \"b\",\n    \"i\",\n    \"u\",\n    \"s\",\n    \"tt\",\n    \"span\",\n    \"sub\",\n    \"sup\",\n    \"big\",\n    \"small\",\n  ])\n  const markup = body\n    // <br> and <br/> → newline\n    .replace(/<br\\s*\\/?>/gi, \"\\n\")\n    // Strip <img> entirely (no visual equivalent in Pango)\n    .replace(/<img\\b[^>]*>/gi, \"\")\n    // Strip <a> open/close tags — keep link text, Pango has no href rendering\n    .replace(/<a\\b[^>]*>/gi, \"\")\n    .replace(/<\\/a>/gi, \"\")\n    // Pass Pango-safe tags through; strip everything else\n    .replace(\n      /<\\/?\\s*([a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*)(\\s[^>]*)?\\s*>/g,\n      (match, tag: string) => (PANGO_SAFE.has(tag.toLowerCase()) ? match : \"\"),\n    )\n  return { markup, hasMarkup: true }\n}\n\nfunction BodyLabel({ body }: { body: string }) {\n  const { markup, hasMarkup } = sanitizeBodyMarkup(body)\n  return (\n    <label\n      class=\"notif-row-body\"\n      label={markup}\n      useMarkup={hasMarkup}\n      halign={1}\n      xalign={0}\n      wrap\n      ellipsize={3}\n    />\n  )\n}\n\nfunction formatTimestamp(unixTime: number): string {\n  const nowSec = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000)\n  const diff = nowSec - unixTime\n  if (diff < 60) return \"just now\"\n  if (diff < 3600) return `${Math.floor(diff / 60)}m ago`\n  if (diff < 86400) return `${Math.floor(diff / 3600)}h ago`\n  return `${Math.floor(diff / 86400)}d ago`\n}\n\nfunction NotificationRow(n: AstalNotifd.Notification) {\n  const isCritical = n.urgency === AstalNotifd.Urgency.CRITICAL\n  return (\n    <box\n      class={`notif-row${isCritical ? \" notif-row-critical\" : \"\"}`}\n      orientation={1}\n      spacing={2}\n    >\n      <box class=\"notif-row-header\" spacing={6}>\n        <label\n          class=\"notif-row-app\"\n          label={n.appName || \"App\"}\n          halign={1}\n          hexpand\n        />\n        <label\n          class=\"notif-row-time\"\n          label={formatTimestamp(n.time)}\n          halign={2}\n        />\n        <button\n          class=\"notif-dismiss-btn\"\n          label=\"󰅖\"\n          onClicked={() => n.dismiss()}\n        />\n      </box>\n      <label\n        class=\"notif-row-summary\"\n        label={n.summary || \"\"}\n        halign={1}\n        xalign={0}\n        wrap\n      />\n      {n.body && <BodyLabel body={n.body} />}\n      {n.actions.length > 0 && (\n        <box class=\"notif-actions\" spacing={4}>\n          {n.actions.map((action) => (\n            <button\n              class=\"notif-action-btn\"\n              label={action.label}\n              hexpand\n              onClicked={() => n.invokeAction(action.id)}\n            />\n          ))}\n        </box>\n      )}\n    </box>\n  )\n}\n\n// --- Clear-all button ---\n\nfunction ClearAllButton() {\n  const notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\n  return (\n    <button\n      class=\"notif-clear-all-btn\"\n      label=\"󰆴  Clear all\"\n      visible={notifications.as((list) => list.length > 0)}\n      onClicked={() => {\n        const list = [...notifd.notifications]\n        list.forEach((n) => n.dismiss())\n        _setUnreadCount(0)\n      }}\n    />\n  )\n}\n\n// --- DND toggle (header button) ---\n\nfunction DndToggle() {\n  const dnd = createBinding(notifd, \"dontDisturb\")\n  return (\n    <button\n      class={dnd.as((on) => `notif-dnd-btn${on ? \" notif-dnd-active\" : \"\"}`)}\n      label={dnd.as((on) => (on ? \"󰂛\" : \"󰂚\"))}\n      tooltipText={dnd.as((on) =>\n        on ? \"DND on — click to disable\" : \"DND off — click to enable\",\n      )}\n      onClicked={() => {\n        notifd.dontDisturb = !notifd.dontDisturb\n      }}\n    />\n  )\n}\n\n// --- Panel window ---\n\nexport function NotificationCenter() {\n  const { TOP, RIGHT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n  const notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\n\n  return (\n    <window\n      name={PANEL_NAME}\n      namespace={PANEL_NAME}\n      visible={false}\n      anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n      marginTop={48}\n      marginRight={8}\n      application={app}\n    >\n      <box class=\"notif-panel\" orientation={1} spacing={0}>\n        <box class=\"notif-panel-header\" spacing={4}>\n          <label\n            class=\"notif-panel-title\"\n            label=\"󰂚  Notifications\"\n            halign={1}\n            hexpand\n          />\n          <ClearAllButton />\n          <DndToggle />\n        </box>\n        <box class=\"notif-panel-list\" orientation={1} spacing={4}>\n          {notifications.as((list) =>\n            list.length === 0\n              ? [\n                  <label\n                    class=\"notif-empty\"\n                    label=\"No notifications\"\n                    halign={3}\n                    valign={3}\n                  />,\n                ]\n              : [...list].reverse().map((n) => NotificationRow(n)),\n          )}\n        </box>\n      </box>\n    </window>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. FULL CONTENT: NotificationToggle.tsx\n\n```typescript\nimport { getUnreadCount, onUnreadChange, toggleNotificationCenter } from \"./NotificationCenter\"\n\nexport function NotificationToggle() {\n  return (\n    <box class=\"notif-toggle-wrap\" valign={3}>\n      <button\n        class=\"utility-button\"\n        label=\"󰂚\"\n        onClicked={() => toggleNotificationCenter()}\n        tooltipText=\"Toggle notifications\"\n      />\n      <label\n        class=\"notif-badge\"\n        visible={false}\n        label=\"\"\n        valign={1}\n        $={(self: any) => {\n          function update() {\n            const count = getUnreadCount()\n            if (count > 0) {\n              self.label = count > 9 ? \"9+\" : String(count)\n              self.visible = true\n            } else {\n              self.label = \"\"\n              self.visible = false\n            }\n          }\n          onUnreadChange(update)\n        }}\n      />\n    </box>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. FULL CONTENT: _notifications.scss\n\n```scss\n@use \"palette\" as *;\n\n// ============================================================\n// Bar toggle button\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-toggle-wrap {\n  position: relative;\n}\n\n// Flat-top hexagon badge (Chrysaki status indicator shape)\n.notif-badge {\n  clip-path: polygon(25% 0%, 75% 0%, 100% 50%, 75% 100%, 25% 100%, 0% 50%);\n  background: $error;\n  color: $text-primary;\n  font-size: 9px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n  min-width: 16px;\n  min-height: 16px;\n  padding: 0px 2px;\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Panel window (glassmorphism — compositor blur provides depth)\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-panel {\n  background-color: rgba(15, 17, 23, 0.15);\n  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);\n  box-shadow: 0 8px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);\n  padding: 10px;\n  min-width: 320px;\n  max-width: 400px;\n}\n\n// --- Panel header ---\n\n.notif-panel-header {\n  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);\n  padding-bottom: 6px;\n  margin-bottom: 4px;\n}\n\n.notif-panel-title {\n  color: $text-primary;\n  font-size: 15px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n  padding: 4px 0px;\n}\n\n.notif-clear-all-btn {\n  background: transparent;\n  border: none;\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 11px;\n  padding: 2px 6px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    color: $error;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-dnd-btn {\n  background: transparent;\n  border: none;\n  color: $text-secondary;\n  font-size: 16px;\n  padding: 2px 4px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    color: $text-primary;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-dnd-active {\n  color: $blonde-light;\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Panel notification list\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-panel-list {\n  padding: 4px 0px;\n}\n\n.notif-empty {\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  padding: 16px 0px;\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Notification row (chamfered Chrysaki container)\n// clip-path produces the 8px chamfer; borders are omitted as\n// clip-path clips them off — use background tint instead.\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-row {\n  clip-path: polygon(\n    8px 0%,\n    calc(100% - 8px) 0%,\n    100% 8px,\n    100% calc(100% - 8px),\n    calc(100% - 8px) 100%,\n    8px 100%,\n    0% calc(100% - 8px),\n    0% 8px\n  );\n  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);\n  padding: 8px 12px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);\n  }\n}\n\n// Urgency modifier: critical notifications get Error red tint\n.notif-row-critical {\n  background: rgba(140, 47, 57, 0.15);\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(140, 47, 57, 0.25);\n  }\n\n  .notif-row-app {\n    color: $blonde-light;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-row-header {\n  margin-bottom: 2px;\n}\n\n.notif-row-app {\n  color: $teal-light;\n  font-size: 11px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n.notif-row-time {\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 10px;\n}\n\n.notif-dismiss-btn {\n  background: transparent;\n  border: none;\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  padding: 0px 2px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    color: $error;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-row-summary {\n  color: $text-primary;\n  font-size: 13px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n.notif-row-body {\n  color: $text-secondary;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  margin-top: 2px;\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Notification action buttons\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-actions {\n  margin-top: 6px;\n  padding-top: 4px;\n  border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);\n}\n\n.notif-action-btn {\n  background: rgba(26, 138, 106, 0.15);\n  border: 1px solid rgba(26, 138, 106, 0.3);\n  color: $emerald-light;\n  font-size: 11px;\n  padding: 3px 8px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(26, 138, 106, 0.3);\n    border-color: $emerald-light;\n    color: $text-primary;\n  }\n\n  &:active {\n    background: rgba(26, 138, 106, 0.45);\n  }\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// Toast popup window (layer-shell, TOP | RIGHT anchor)\n// High alpha background: toasts float without compositor blur.\n// ============================================================\n\n.notif-toast-list {\n  padding: 0px;\n}\n\n// Chamfered toast card — matches .notif-row shape at larger scale\n.notif-toast {\n  clip-path: polygon(\n    8px 0%,\n    calc(100% - 8px) 0%,\n    100% 8px,\n    100% calc(100% - 8px),\n    calc(100% - 8px) 100%,\n    8px 100%,\n    0% calc(100% - 8px),\n    0% 8px\n  );\n  background: rgba(28, 31, 43, 0.92); // $surface at high alpha\n  padding: 10px 14px;\n  min-width: 300px;\n  max-width: 380px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(37, 40, 54, 0.95); // $raised at high alpha\n  }\n}\n\n// Urgency modifier: critical toasts get Error red background\n.notif-toast-critical {\n  background: rgba(140, 47, 57, 0.88);\n\n  &:hover {\n    background: rgba(181, 63, 74, 0.92);\n  }\n\n  .notif-toast-app {\n    color: $blonde-light;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-toast-header {\n  margin-bottom: 3px;\n}\n\n.notif-toast-app {\n  color: $emerald-light;\n  font-size: 11px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n.notif-toast-close {\n  background: transparent;\n  border: none;\n  color: $text-muted;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  padding: 0px 2px;\n  min-width: 0px;\n\n  &:hover {\n    color: $error;\n  }\n}\n\n.notif-toast-summary {\n  color: $text-primary;\n  font-size: 13px;\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n.notif-toast-body {\n  color: $text-secondary;\n  font-size: 12px;\n  margin-top: 2px;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. TOAST-RELATED FILES\n\nNo existing `Toast` or `Toast`-related files exist. The toast styles are defined in `_notifications.scss` (lines 202–280), but the TypeScript component `NotificationToast.tsx` has not yet been created.\n\n---\n\n### 7. FULL CONTENT: style.scss\n\n```scss\n@use \"styles/palette\" as *;\n@use \"styles/glass\" as *;\n@use \"styles/bar\";\n@use \"styles/workspaces\";\n@use \"styles/clock\";\n@use \"styles/battery\";\n@use \"styles/powermenu\";\n@use \"styles/should-have\";\n@use \"styles/active-window\";\n@use \"styles/pulseaudio\";\n@use \"styles/utility-buttons\";\n@use \"styles/services\";\n@use \"styles/notifications\";\n\n* {\n  font-family: \"Space Grotesk\", \"IosevkaTermSlab Nerd Font\", monospace;\n  font-size: 13px;\n}\n\nwindow {\n  background: transparent;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. EXAMPLE WINDOW COMPONENTS\n\n#### ServicePanel (ServiceStatus.tsx, lines 164–184)\nA modal panel with TOP | RIGHT anchor showing service health indicators:\n```typescript\nexport function ServicePanel() {\n  const { TOP, RIGHT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n\n  return (\n    <window\n      name={PANEL_NAME}\n      namespace={PANEL_NAME}\n      visible={false}\n      anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n      marginTop={48}\n      marginRight={8}\n      application={app}\n    >\n      <box class=\"svc-panel\" orientation={1} spacing={4}>\n        <label class=\"svc-panel-title\" label={\"\\u{F0614}  Services\"} halign={1} />\n        {SERVICES.map((svc) => ServiceRow(svc))}\n      </box>\n    </window>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n#### NotificationCenter (NotificationCenter.tsx, lines 194–237)\nAnother modal panel at TOP | RIGHT:\n```typescript\nexport function NotificationCenter() {\n  const { TOP, RIGHT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n  const notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\n\n  return (\n    <window\n      name={PANEL_NAME}\n      namespace={PANEL_NAME}\n      visible={false}\n      anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n      marginTop={48}\n      marginRight={8}\n      application={app}\n    >\n      <box class=\"notif-panel\" orientation={1} spacing={0}>\n        {/* panel content */}\n      </box>\n    </window>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n#### BarLeft (per-monitor persistent bar)\nPer-monitor bars are created per the `app.get_monitors()` loop in `app.ts`:\n```typescript\nexport function BarLeft(gdkmonitor: Gdk.Monitor) {\n  const { TOP, LEFT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n\n  return (\n    <window\n      visible\n      name=\"chrysaki-bar-left\"\n      namespace=\"chrysaki-bar-left\"\n      gdkmonitor={gdkmonitor}\n      anchor={TOP | LEFT}\n      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n      marginTop={0}\n      marginLeft={8}\n      application={app}\n    >\n      {/* bar content */}\n    </window>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n**Key pattern**: Persistent bars (like BarLeft, BarRight, BarCenter) are visible by default and per-monitor. Modal panels (like NotificationCenter, ServicePanel) are initially hidden and toggled by button clicks.\n\n---\n\n### 9. ASTAL/NOTIFD API USAGE PATTERNS\n\n#### Import Pattern\n```typescript\nimport AstalNotifd from \"gi://AstalNotifd\"\nconst notifd = AstalNotifd.get_default()!\n```\n\n#### Other Astal Services (examples from codebase)\n```typescript\n// Network\nimport AstalNetwork from \"gi://AstalNetwork\"\nconst network = AstalNetwork.get_default()!\n\n// Media (MPRIS)\nimport AstalMpris from \"gi://AstalMpris\"\nconst mpris = AstalMpris.get_default()!\n```\n\n#### createBinding Pattern (Reactive Property Binding)\n```typescript\nimport { createBinding, createComputed } from \"ags\"\n\n// Bind to a GObject property\nconst notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\nconst dnd = createBinding(notifd, \"dontDisturb\")\n\n// Use in JSX via .as() to transform the binding\nvisible={notifications.as((list) => list.length > 0)}\nlabel={dnd.as((on) => (on ? \"󰂛\" : \"󰂚\"))}\n```\n\n#### Signal Connection Pattern\n```typescript\nnotifd.connect(\"notified\", () => {\n  _setUnreadCount(_unreadCount + 1)\n})\n```\n\n#### Accessing Notification Properties\n```typescript\nfunction NotificationRow(n: AstalNotifd.Notification) {\n  const isCritical = n.urgency === AstalNotifd.Urgency.CRITICAL\n  return (\n    <box>\n      <label label={n.appName || \"App\"} />\n      <label label={n.summary || \"\"} />\n      {n.body && <BodyLabel body={n.body} />}\n      {n.actions.length > 0 && (\n        <box class=\"notif-actions\">\n          {n.actions.map((action) => (\n            <button\n              label={action.label}\n              onClicked={() => n.invokeAction(action.id)}\n            />\n          ))}\n        </box>\n      )}\n      <button onClicked={() => n.dismiss()} />\n    </box>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n#### Window Anchors & Properties\n```typescript\nimport { Astal } from \"ags/gtk4\"\n\nconst { TOP, RIGHT, LEFT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n\n<window\n  name=\"panel-name\"\n  namespace=\"panel-name\"\n  visible={false}\n  anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n  exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n  marginTop={48}\n  marginRight={8}\n  application={app}\n>\n  {/* content */}\n</window>\n```\n\n#### createPoll Pattern (Polling/Time-based Updates)\n```typescript\nimport { createPoll } from \"ags/time\"\n\nconst time = createPoll(\"00:00\", 1000, () => {\n  return `󰥔  ${GLib.DateTime.new_now_local()!.format(\"%H:%M\")!}`\n})\n\n<label label={time} />\n```\n\n#### createComputed Pattern (Derived State)\n```typescript\nimport { createComputed } from \"ags\"\n\nconst isOk = createComputed(() => status().trim() === \"ok\")\nconst statusClass = createComputed(() =>\n  isOk() ? \"svc-panel-healthy\" : \"svc-panel-unhealthy\"\n)\n\n<image class={statusClass} />\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Key Takeaways for Toast Implementation:**\n\n1. **NotificationToast.tsx** must be created in `/home/kiriketsuki/dots/chrysaki-ralph-ags-notification-center-T10/ags/.config/ags/widgets/`\n\n2. **API Access**: Use `notifd` (already exported from `NotificationCenter.tsx`) to listen for notifications and iterate over `notifd.notifications`.\n\n3. **Window Properties**: Toast should use `TOP | RIGHT` anchor with `exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}` to float above other windows without reserving space. Higher `marginTop` than the panel (48px) to avoid collision.\n\n4. **Styling**: CSS classes `.notif-toast`, `.notif-toast-critical`, `.notif-toast-app`, `.notif-toast-summary`, `.notif-toast-body`, `.notif-toast-close` are already defined in `_notifications.scss` (lines 207–279). Use chamfered clip-path matching the panel rows.\n\n5. **Reactive Patterns**: Use `createBinding()` for property reactions, `createComputed()` for derived state, `createPoll()` for time-based updates, and direct signal connections (`notifd.connect()`) for event handling.\n\n6. **Color Palette**: Access via `$palette` SCSS variables. Emerald-light for accents, error for critical urgency, text-primary/secondary for content."}],"totalDurationMs":131025,"totalTokens":101900,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1940,"cache_read_input_tokens":92383,"output_tokens":7574,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1940},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PqhnJrm8wvPX7rmWnSgzPV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need to implement `NotificationToast.tsx`. Let me analyze what's needed:\n\n**Task T10 Requirements** (from Known Issues in spec.md):\n- Layer-shell window (TOP | RIGHT anchor, marginTop 48, marginRight 8) — but wait, it should be at the TOP | RIGHT with some margin, and needs to not collide with the panel. Looking at the spec again: \"marginTop 48, marginRight 8\"\n- DND-aware enqueue — if DND is on, don't show toasts\n- GLib.timeout_add 5000ms auto-dismiss\n\n\n- MAX_VISIBLE=4 FIFO overflow queue with a ToastRow component for each notification\n- Critical urgency class wired to apply the notif-toast-critical styling\n\nSo the structure is: a layer-shell window positioned at the top-right corner that manages a queue of up to 4 visible toasts, automatically dismissing each one after 5 seconds, while respecting Do Not Disturb mode.\n\nFor the reactive implementation, I'll import the existing `notifd` object from NotificationCenter and use GLib timers for auto-dismiss. The key is managing two lists—one for active toasts currently displayed and another for pending ones waiting in the queue. When a notification arrives and DND is off, it goes into the active list if there's room, otherwise into the pending queue. Once a toast is dismissed, I pull the next one from the queue to fill that spot.\n\nFor state management in AGS, I'm going to follow the listener pattern already used in NotificationCenter—keeping module-level arrays for active and queued toasts, then using callbacks to trigger JSX updates whenever the state changes. Setting up the toast system with a module-level queue to track active notifications, then using the setup callback to subscribe to notification changes and update the display widget imperatively when the list changes.\n\nWriting the toast implementation... I'm implementing the dismissal logic to remove a toast from the active list, then promoting the next queued notification if there's space available, and scheduling its auto-dismiss timer. Setting up the timeout callback...\n\nBuilding the toast UI component... Writing the notification window component... I'm realizing the JSX in AGS creates actual GTK widgets, so `ToastRow(n)` returns a widget I can append directly to the box. Since the toast list changes dynamically, I need an imperative approach rather than relying on reactive bindings like in NotificationCenter. Let me look more carefully at how AGS handles this pattern.\n\nThe `$` prop is actually the key here — it's an imperative setup function that runs on the created widget, so I can subscribe to my custom state changes and rebuild the contents when the active toasts list updates. I should also manage the window's visibility so it hides when there are no active toasts, rather than showing an empty window.\n\nBuilding the toast window implementation... I'm running into a question about how JSX elements work in AGS when called outside of JSX context — when I invoke `ToastRow(n)` directly in the rebuild function, does it return the actual widget or do I need to handle the conversion differently? Looking at how `NotificationRow` is used elsewhere in the codebase, it seems to be called within JSX expressions, so I need to figure out if there's a different pattern for calling these functions programmatically. I'm realizing that `ToastRow(n)` returns a GTK widget directly since JSX in AGS compiles down to widget construction, so appending it should work fine. Now I need to verify the signal signature for the \"notified\" event in AstalNotifd to make sure I'm handling the notification ID correctly.\n\nLooking at the available signals, I should handle both \"notified\" when new notifications arrive and \"resolved\" when they're dismissed externally, so the toast system stays in sync with the notification state.\n\nSetting up the toast module... Writing notification handlers... Writing the toast component... Writing the notification toast component...\n\nI'm noticing a potential issue with how `onToastChange` is being called in the `NotificationToast` function—it needs to be set up properly to trigger the rebuild whenever the active toasts change. of `onToastChange` and the JSX evaluation. The function runs synchronously: first `onToastChange(rebuild)` registers the listener, then the JSX creates the widgets and triggers the `$` callbacks that set `listBox` and `toastWin`. Since notifications arrive asynchronously later, both variables are guaranteed to be initialized by the time `rebuild()` actually runs.\n\nBut there's a timing concern — if a notification arrives before the window is created, `rebuild()` has an early return guard that safely handles the null case. The real question is whether the module-level connection to `notifd` happens before or after `NotificationToast()` is called during app startup.\n\nLooking at the sequence: the module imports first and sets up the listener, then `app.start` triggers `main()` which calls `NotificationToast()` to initialize the window and register the callback. So by the time notifications can arrive, everything's wired up correctly.\n\nNow I need to check how AGS handles timeout removal — whether it uses `GLib.SOURCE_REMOVE` or just `false`. I need to figure out the right signal to listen for when a notification is dismissed. The `dismiss()` method should trigger something on the notifd side, but I'm not entirely certain whether it's `resolved` or another signal name. Let me approach this by relying on the notification object's own state changes rather than guessing at the signal name. The spec says we need to handle auto-dismiss. The key requirements are:\n1. Toast appears for 5 seconds then auto-dismisses (removes from toast window)\n2. User can manually close by clicking the close button\n3. DND prevents toasts from appearing\n\nFor simplicity, let me just handle our own dismiss logic. If a notification is dismissed from the notification center panel (via `n.dismiss()`), the notifd service will fire the \"resolved\" signal on the global notifd object. We should listen to that to clean up our toast list.\n\nI need to check the exact signal signature. Looking at the AstalNotifd.Notifd API, the resolved signal passes the notification ID and a ClosedReason. I'll set up a listener that removes dismissed notifications from both the active and queued toast lists, then promotes any waiting toasts and triggers an update. I need to verify that `notifd.get_notification(id)` actually exists as a method on the AstalNotifd object, since I'm planning to use it to retrieve the notification by its ID when the signal fires. I'll use `notifd.get_notification(id)` since the spec explicitly mentions it as the idiomatic API. For the window behavior, I should hide it when the toast list is empty to avoid any interaction issues. Now I need to finalize the implementation and handle the rebuild case properly.\n\nLet me trace through the initialization order: when `app.ts` imports `NotificationToast`, the module-level code runs first, registering the signal handlers and initializing the state arrays. Then when `app.start()` is called and `NotificationToast()` executes, the window gets created. The `if (!listBox) return` guard protects against rebuild being called before the window exists.\n\nWriting the notification daemon file... Writing notification queue logic... Writing the notification window component...\n\nNow I'm thinking through potential issues with the implementation—checking that GLib imports correctly since AGS uses gjs, and verifying that the notification retrieval method exists on the Notifd object as expected. I'm verifying that calling `ToastRow(n)` as a function returns the compiled GTK widget correctly, which should work fine with `listBox.append()`. The `marginTop` positioning won't conflict since NotificationCenter is hidden by default and only appears on click, while the toast displays independently.\n\nNow I need to check how the notification signal is connected — looking at NotificationCenter.tsx, the `notifd.connect(\"notified\", ...)` handler is set up at the module level to listen for incoming notifications.\n\nSince I'm importing `notifd` from NotificationCenter in my NotificationToast file and both files connect to the same signal, GLib will handle multiple handlers just fine. The key thing is making sure there's no circular dependency — NotificationCenter exports `notifd` at the top level, and since both files get imported by app.ts before anything runs, the order should work out.\n\nNow I need to figure out the GLib import situation. The existing AGS codebase doesn't seem to import GLib explicitly, probably relying on AGS's built-in utilities like `createPoll` for timing. Let me check what I actually need...\n\nFor this TypeScript/GJS setup, GLib should be accessible via the standard `import GLib from \"gi://GLib\"` pattern, same as the other GObject imports in the codebase. The `GLib.timeout_add` API takes a priority, interval in milliseconds, and a callback that returns either `GLib.SOURCE_REMOVE` or `GLib.SOURCE_CONTINUE` to control whether the timeout repeats. That's the right approach here, so I'm ready to implement it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8018,"cache_read_input_tokens":55690,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8018},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87de7f8a-1210-4ae0-aa43-0a98da4aea22","uuid":"aab1c30c-d244-4091-b190-4af0f9fbf6eb"}
